OL,6,F"What was apparent, it transpired, was
OL,7,Fthat it must have been a man who had
OL,8,Fbeen sawn into pieces.
OL,10,F"As you will hear, 27 pieces.
OL,12,F"That initial gruesome finding was to
OL,13,Ftrigger investigations that led to, a
OL,14,Fnumber of weeks later, April 27 and 28
OL,15,Fand May 1, further parts, including
OL,16,Fparts of his skull and ear, over
OL,17,Fvarious locations in the Greater
OL,18,FManchester area.
OL,20,F"This case is about who that man was.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@AOU|D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
