OL,6,FJurors were told only around one third
OL,7,Fof Mr Everett's body was recovered.
OL,9,FBack at their home address, officers
OL,10,Ffound blood-staining in the kitchen
OL,11,Fand a piece of cut-out carpet from the
OL,12,Fdefendant's bedroom, the court was
OL,13,Ftold.
OL,15,FPathology of the skull fragments
OL,16,Fshowed Mr Everett had been subject to
OL,17,Fa "sustained, severe blunt force
OL,18,Fphysical assault", with repeated blows
OL,19,Fto his head, shattering and fracturing
OL,20,Fhis skull.
